hooer
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a contemptible person, difficult thing, etc. [a var. pron. of whore]


Origin: [none]
Register: informal
Register 2: derogatory
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: also hua
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1953 16 M A34 Thames DHS 27 HOORIN (HOURIN) 1953 17 M A39 Thames DHS 27 HOORIN (HOURIN).] ca1926 Dunedin and Central Otago as an address to men etc.
